Defendant Michael K Kern in court with attorney Lisa M. Procaccio.  Defendant Michael K Kern in custody.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, and defendant. 
 
AS TO COUNTS 2 AND 3:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction AS TO EACH COUNT with Huber release to the day reporting center for programming.  Counts 2 and 3 are Consecutive to each other and with any other time being served.  Credit of 130 days granted as to Count 2.  Credit of 0 days as to Count 3.  NO Electronic Monitoring as to either Count. 

The Court STAYED these sentences and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 18 MONTHS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzer tests;
*No illegal drugs or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Obtain Mental health assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment- if prescribed take any prescription medication only in the manner/dosage     as prescribed by a treating physician;
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*No contact with victims Johnathon T., Heather S., Lekemberell M.;
*Perform 25 hours of community service;
*Participate in Cognitive thinking program;
*Obtain/maintain employment to the extent allowable by social security administration as to not affect payments;
*Obtain GED or HSED;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, costs, fees, and assessments by the end of supervision period or any remaining balance shall convert to civil judgment.  

The state in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court ordered restitution set at zero as to all three victims.  The Court grants expungement ONLY if the defendant successfully completes each and every term/condition of probation during the probation period.  Appeal rights given by the Court. 
